cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with a problem related to graph coloring and graph algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. 

- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the computational complexity of a graph problem. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the NP-completeness of the problem for a specific value of c. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper mentions the restriction of input graphs to connected planar bipartite graphs of maximum degree 3. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the problem of swapping colored tokens can be seen as a game between the vertices of the graph. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with a problem related to graph coloring, which is a topic in discrete mathematics.
